{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":565481,"duration_api_ms":696299,"num_turns":19,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5b3617f8-2a07-4a50-8a08-daa23ce5e3ea","total_cost_usd":1.2254569500000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":16,"cache_creation_input_tokens":50457,"cache_read_input_tokens":583174,"output_tokens":7541,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":50457,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":16,"outputTokens":7541,"cacheReadInputTokens":583174,"cacheCreationInputTokens":50457,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7955482500000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":2006,"outputTokens":16146,"cacheReadInputTokens":1960827,"cacheCreationInputTokens":120872,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.42990870000000003,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"In `safe_plan_hash_backfill` (fs.rs:2628-2649), when the entry was created BEFORE any plan was persisted, both `plan_hash` and `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` are `None`. If a plan is later persisted and then the entry is revisited (via `update_task_run` or re-`record_task_run_start`), the backfill correctly refuses because `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` is `None` (legacy guard). However, this means entries created in a no-plan-yet state can NEVER be auto-populated from the snapshot, even though the system now knows which plan is executing. The acceptance criterion says 'Lineage entries auto-populate plan_hash from the milestone snapshot when callers omit it' — this edge case (start before plan, complete after plan) is not covered. Consider: when `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` is `None` AND `plan_hash` is `None` AND the entry is still Running (not terminal), it is safe to populate both `plan_hash` and `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` from the current snapshot during revisitation, since no prior plan version existed to conflict with.","rationale":"The safe_plan_hash_backfill provenance guard is correct for entries created after a plan exists, but it creates a dead zone for entries created before any plan. In workflows where beads are dispatched before persist_plan is called (e.g., the first cycle of a milestone), these entries will permanently lack plan_hash linkage despite the plan becoming known later. The fix is small and safe: only Running entries with both fields None qualify, and there's no evolution risk since no plan existed at creation."}],"summary":"All three issues from the project prompt are addressed. Issue 1 (journal struct drift) was resolved in a prior round by unifying the structs and adding round-trip tests. Issue 2 (runless-to-named rejection) is fixed via the started_at pre-filter and backfill logic. Issue 3 (plan_hash auto-population) is implemented with snapshot auto-population at creation and safe_plan_hash_backfill with provenance tracking. All 683 tests pass. The debug_assert→runtime guard change in unique_terminal_replay_match is a reasonable production safety improvement. One edge case identified: entries created before any plan exists get snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=None and can never be backfilled, even when a plan is later persisted and the entry is revisited while still Running."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"57bb415d-eeda-4c20-994d-7c5800668455"}
